{
  "stem": "19550.9",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This to me is above all the purpose of the-- of survival and, in a way, the compensation, to the extent that one can speak of compensation at all for what the Holocaust has wrought, and what we had gone through collectively and individually.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My oldest and youngest sister of course and my mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My mother and my youngest sister that I have told you were unfortunately murdered and-- on arrival to Auschwitz, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in what probably was in a way the most execrable way in which the Holocaust was operated in those days.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, you know, the-- the gas chambers and the-- and the crematoria were not up to handling 2/3 of Hungarian Jewry.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In less than six weeks, over 600,000 people were deported.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's-- the-- the mind has to be boggled by the sheer numbers of it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- and so, you know, the-- the operation was if at all possible, more [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] horrible.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Open fires, this was, you know-- people being shot in the air, children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[SIGHS] It has-- [SIGHS] the-- the-- the vision of that hell has-- it will never leave me, of course.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As the whole Holocaust cannot leave me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I'm-- I am, in a way, as everybody else must be, imprisoned by it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you can never be liberated from it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But in a very direct, personal way, it has prevented me for years from having a child.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I could not free myself of the sight and the sound and-- and the odor and what I have seen and felt.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
